The incident photon to current efficiency (IPCE) at each wavelength was determined by using illumination from a 300-W Xenon arc lamp (CEAULIGHT). The monochromatic light was produced using a monochromator (Beijing 7-star optical instruments-7ISW75) with a 10-nm bandpass. The light intensity (Pλ) at each wavelength (λ) was determined with a THORLABS S120VC power meter. The IPCE value was calculated using the equation:1IPCE(%)=1240×(Jlight−Jdark)λ×Pλ×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{IPCE}}({\mathrm{\% }}) = \frac{{1240 \times (J_{{\mathrm{light}}} - J_{{\mathrm{dark}}})}}{{\lambda \times P_\lambda }} \times 100{\mathrm{\% }}$$\end{document}

The applied bias photo-to-current efficiency (ABPE) was calculated based on the current-potential curves under 1 sun, AM1.5 G illumination,2ABPE(%)=(Jlight−Jdark)×(1.23−VRHE)Plight×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{ABPE}}({\mathrm{\% }}) = \frac{{(J_{{\mathrm{light}}} - J_{{\mathrm{dark}}}) \times (1.23 - V_{{\mathrm{RHE}}})}}{{P_{{\mathrm{light}}}}} \times 100{\mathrm{\% }}$$\end{document}With VRHE is the applied potential versus RHE, Jlight and Jdark the measured photocurrent and dark current, respectively. Plight is the power density of the lamp, AM 1.5 G (100 mW cm−2).

The amounts of oxygen and hydrogen evolution were determined by gas chromatography. Before the measurement, the sealed electrolytic cell was degassed with Argon for 15 min to remove residual air. The amount of oxygen and hydrogen evolution after 2 h of electrolysis at 0.2 V vs. NHE was measured. The Faradaic efficiency was calculated according to the integrated charge (Q) passed and the amount of O2 evolved using the equation:3η(%)=96485×nO2×4Q×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
